body:
Right now the icon is the Dart logo, which is fairly overloaded icon. I wonder if we can make a specific icon for Observatory.

strawman: Perhaps a telescope?

comment_data.body: Totally agree the Dart icon is overloaded in IntelliJ. Sorry I don't have any better suggestions yet.

Hm, I wonder if part of the challenge here is that "Open Observatory" is really a solution to many different user intents: CPU Profile, VM Debug, Memory profile, etc. We could have icons for each one of those, which would be a bit more specific.

In the meantime, https://material.io/icons/#ic_developer_board is an idea.

I'm happy to commission an icon, too. The literal idea that comes to mind: "an observatory with a telescope".

What do yall think?

The developer board is similar to what my mental picture was. I also thought of a microscope because the tool is sorta dissecting your program and putting it under a microscope (but not really). Other things to consider:
- IDEA has buttons for Run, Debug, Profile that people are familiar with that could provide visual clues
- The button launches you out of IntelliJ, into the browser where the Observatory UI runs

Perhaps you're thinking of something [like this,](https://d18gmz9e98r8v5.cloudfront.net/ptr/20140703201303_938669017_1148_9.jpg) using the structure as inspiration for an icon.

+1 to developer board
+1 to an observatory / telescope / microscope
If developer board works, then I don't need to commision a new icon. So let me know if that doesn't work. :)
@devoncarew can we use the material icons, such as the https://material.io/icons/#ic_developer_board one, as-is?
Yeah, or we could colorize it a bit if that would help it fit in better with the other icons.
Hmm, it doesn't grab me: I'm not sure that there's an icon that would jump out at me as a 'click to open the observatory' icon.

Just got a new idea, how about an 'eye' icon?
https://material.io/icons/#ic_remove_red_eye

OK, like the eye of Sauron?

There's also this guy: https://material.io/icons/#ic_wb_incandescent
I like eye and timer. Incandescent seems hard to decode.

And, cycling back to this comment:

> if part of the challenge here is that "Open Observatory" is really a solution to many different user intents: CPU Profile, VM Debug, Memory profile, etc. We could have icons for each one of those, which would be a bit more specific

I do think that we would be better off offering different entry-points for specific actions that a user wants to take, and not a big-bucket "Open Observatory" action.
